176. Second Highest Salary

select(
select distinct salary 
from Employee
order by salary desc
limit 1 offset 1
)as SecondHighestSalary ;

keywords usage:

distinct is used to return only unique values by removing duplicate rows from the result set.
order by is used to sort the table based on a particular coloumn .
desc- sort in descending order 
limit give me only N rows from the result.
OFFSET is used to skip a number of rows before starting to return results.